[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Most Common Mistakes in Chess"]
[ChapterName "Mistake 6: Not punishing your opponent"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xx2nOKJv/oOpJ3VCu"]
[FEN "r1bqk1nr/pppp1ppp/2n5/2b1p3/2B1P3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/RNBQ1RK1 b kq - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.07.21"]
[UTCTime "03:10:33"]

1... f6 { A common beginner's opening mistake. This cannot go unpunished. } 2. d3?! (2. c3! Nge7 3. d4 { Rule of thumb: If black ever plays f6 in the e4 e5 lines, must play d4 ASAP to open up the center, thus exposing Black's weak f6 move in daylight. }) 2... Nge7 { Hard to punish Black's horrible f6 at this moment. } *


[Event "🔥🔥: Mistake 7: Grabbing too much material at a risk"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/study/fNOVLINj/lQa9QM41"]
[Date "2020.07.21"]
