[StudyName "Most Common Mistakes in Chess"]
[ChapterName "Mistake 9: Trading bishop for knight incorrectly"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xx2nOKJv/JoC0TTnJ"]
[FEN "1r3rk1/p1bb1ppp/2np4/2p1p3/2P4q/P2QPBN1/1P1P1PPP/R1B1K2R w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.07.21"]
[UTCTime "03:10:33"]

1. Bxc6? { White has seemingly logical intentions of trading bishop for knight and then closing up the center with e4, with plans of rerouting the knight to d5 way way down the road. However, it comes with severe consequences, the lack of control over the light squares... } 1... Bxc6 2. e4 f5! { Suddenly, the center explodes, and the light squares are extremely vulnerable for White. The plan of maneuvering the knight to d5 is out the door. } *


