{ Black is up an exchange (rook for knight) and an extra pawn. It is important to be willing to give some material back if necessary to achieve a decisive advantage. }
24... Rhf8 (24... f5! { Giving back a pawn to free up the position and shut down the f5 outpost from White's knight. } 25. exf5 (25. Qxf5 Rdf8) 25... Rhf8 26. Ne3 e4 { And Black is still up a healthy exchange and a more active position. }) 25. Ne3 Qh7 26. Nf5 { It is unclear how Black can make progress with this annoying knight on f5, which arguably is stronger than a rook at the moment. } *


