[Event "🔥🔥: Mistake 15: Blindly following general chess principles"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/study/fNOVLINj/ZJ2OcNxQ"]
[Date "2020.07.21"]
[Result "*"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Mr_Penings"]
[Variant "From Position"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Most Common Mistakes in Chess"]
[ChapterName "Mistake 15: Blindly following general chess principles"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xx2nOKJv/MMAzQvYL"]
[FEN "r4k2/pp2q2p/2npb1p1/2p5/2P1P3/2NP2P1/P5BP/1R1Q2K1 w - - 0 16"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.07.21"]
[UTCTime "03:10:33"]

{ The general rule is knights belong on outposts. d5 is an outpost by definition, and a common mistake is to blindly follow these principles. }
16. Nd5? (16. e5! { A better continuation to achieve the superior minor piece } 16... dxe5 (16... Nxe5?! 17. Rxb7) 17. Bxc6 bxc6 18. Qf3+) 16... Bxd5 17. exd5 Nd4 { Wait a second... now black has the knight on an outpost and White has a terrible bishop. White gets punished for blindly following the rules without second thought. } *


