{ Black has the bishop pair, and wisely should control the h1-a8 diagonal. }
10... Bb7? { The right idea, but it fails because White closes the diagonal first with d4 } (10... d4! { Playing d4 first is a must here if Black wants to control the long diagonal. Knight is forced to move, and only then is Bb7 accurate } 11. Ne2 Bb7) 11. d4 cxd4 12. Nb5 { And the diagonal is now shut down for as long as White desires. } *


[Event "🔥🔥: Mistake 18: Unequal trades against higher rated players"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/study/fNOVLINj/LZiuG5LY"]
[Date "2020.07.21"]
[Result "*"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Mr_Penings"]
